text: == Incumbents == * President - Árpád Göncz * Prime Minister - József Antall (until 12 December), Péter Boross (starting 12 December) == Events == *April 3 - Hungary's first attempt to enter the Eurovision Song Contest ends in failure, as Andrea Szulák fails to win a place in the final rounds. *August 15 - The Hungarian Grand Prix is held at the Hungaroring in Budapest and is won by Damon Hill. ==Births== *January 19 - Bence Biczó, swimmer ==Deaths== *February - Gusztáv Bene, boxer (born 1911) ==References== Category:1990s in Hungary Hungary Hungary
title: 1993 in Hungary
